[
  {
    "startTime": 4.2,
    "endTime": 6.25,
    "text": "Welcome to the Good Morning show."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 6.25,
    "endTime": 10.58,
    "text": "In today's program we're going to be talking\nto Hillary Clinton."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 10.58,
    "endTime": 12.98,
    "text": "Oh, I'm sorry."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 12.98,
    "endTime": 14.9,
    "text": "That's the wrong picture."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 14.9,
    "endTime": 17.119,
    "text": "We've clearly made a mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.12,
    "endTime": 18.12,
    "text": "Argh!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.56,
    "endTime": 28.08,
    "text": "Hi everyone, I'm Vicki and I'm British."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.09,
    "endTime": 30.61,
    "text": "And I'm Jay and I'm American."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 30.61,
    "endTime": 36.14,
    "text": "And this lessons about things you can say\nwhen you make mistakes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.14,
    "endTime": 37.42,
    "text": "Where should we start?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.42,
    "endTime": 42.050000000000004,
    "text": "Well the first thing we say is often an expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.05,
    "endTime": 43.449999999999996,
    "text": "She means expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.45,
    "endTime": 44.45,
    "text": "Expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 44.45,
    "endTime": 49.760000000000005,
    "text": "The pronunciation's different in British\nand American."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 49.76,
    "endTime": 51.75,
    "text": "Say expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.75,
    "endTime": 56.57,
    "text": "An expletive is a word that shows you're\nangry or upset."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.57,
    "endTime": 57.63,
    "text": "Argh!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.63,
    "endTime": 58.690000000000005,
    "text": "Argh!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.69,
    "endTime": 59.75,
    "text": "Oh…."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.75,
    "endTime": 63.53,
    "text": "The next thing you'd say is not polite."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 63.53,
    "endTime": 67.92,
    "text": "Yeah, expletives are generally rude words."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 67.92,
    "endTime": 70.49,
    "text": "I'm sure you know these ones."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 70.49,
    "endTime": 72.82,
    "text": "They're common curse words."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 72.82,
    "endTime": 76.05999999999999,
    "text": "Be careful though because they are very rude."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.06,
    "endTime": 82.07000000000001,
    "text": "Yes, don't say them to your boss or people\nyou don't know well."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.07,
    "endTime": 84.24,
    "text": "What are some polite alternatives?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 84.24,
    "endTime": 85.259,
    "text": "Hmm."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.26,
    "endTime": 93.58000000000001,
    "text": "I've heard some people say 'oh bother',\nbut that's normally if it's a small thing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.009,
    "endTime": 99.18,
    "text": "Oh bother, I've spilt my tea."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 99.189,
    "endTime": 102.439,
    "text": "'Bother' sounds very British."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.44,
    "endTime": 104.85,
    "text": "In the US we might say 'shoot'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 106.16,
    "endTime": 111.1,
    "text": "Oh shoot, I left my wallet at home."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 111.1,
    "endTime": 115.20899999999999,
    "text": "Again, we say this for small mistakes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 115.209,
    "endTime": 122.02000000000001,
    "text": "Yes, if you want to add some emotion, I think\n'damn' is a useful word."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.02,
    "endTime": 123.06,
    "text": "Is it rude?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.06,
    "endTime": 129.63,
    "text": "It's a little rude but it's better than\nthe curse words if you're at work or something,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 129.63,
    "endTime": 132.95,
    "text": "and it shows you're upset."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.95,
    "endTime": 134.39,
    "text": "Oh damn."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 134.39,
    "endTime": 138.2,
    "text": "I forgot to put petrol in the car."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.12,
    "endTime": 140.26,
    "text": "Damn."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 140.26,
    "endTime": 141.64999999999998,
    "text": "I just made a mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 141.65,
    "endTime": 142.65,
    "text": "What?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.65,
    "endTime": 148.0,
    "text": "I just sent everyone the wrong dates for the\nmeeting."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 148.0,
    "endTime": 152.689,
    "text": "Notice that Jay said 'I just made a mistake'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.689,
    "endTime": 155.98,
    "text": "We use the verb 'make' with mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 155.98,
    "endTime": 160.659,
    "text": "In some languages it's do a mistake',\nbut not in English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 160.659,
    "endTime": 166.31,
    "text": "Yes, so don't make that mistake with mistake!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.31,
    "endTime": 169.969,
    "text": "'Make' and 'mistake' both start with the letter\nm."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.969,
    "endTime": 172.53,
    "text": "Perhaps that will help you remember."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 172.53,
    "endTime": 173.53,
    "text": "OK."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.53,
    "endTime": 177.25,
    "text": "Now are there other ways to say 'I've\nmade a mistake'?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.25,
    "endTime": 178.51,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.51,
    "endTime": 180.79,
    "text": "We often use phrasal verbs."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.79,
    "endTime": 183.62,
    "text": "Let's see one in action."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 185.02,
    "endTime": 188.82000000000002,
    "text": "Oh no, I've screwed up again!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.829,
    "endTime": 190.40900000000002,
    "text": "What have you done?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.409,
    "endTime": 194.19,
    "text": "I forgot to press save before I closed the\ndocument."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 194.19,
    "endTime": 199.26,
    "text": "He's always screwing up like that."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 199.26,
    "endTime": 201.189,
    "text": "The verb is 'screw up'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 201.189,
    "endTime": 204.62,
    "text": "It's slang and it's a bit rude."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 204.62,
    "endTime": 208.48000000000002,
    "text": "Again, you probably don't want to say it\nto your boss."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 208.5,
    "endTime": 213.94,
    "text": "But there's another verb you could use instead\n– mess up."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.12,
    "endTime": 223.72,
    "text": "Oh. Can I try it?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 223.73,
    "endTime": 225.569,
    "text": "OK but be careful."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.569,
    "endTime": 228.819,
    "text": "It's taken me ages to get this far."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.82,
    "endTime": 230.76,
    "text": "Don't mess it up."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.84,
    "endTime": 231.86,
    "text": "OK."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 235.34,
    "endTime": 238.719,
    "text": "…\nOh sorry"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.719,
    "endTime": 241.84,
    "text": "Mess up means to do something badly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 241.84,
    "endTime": 248.049,
    "text": "It's a phrasal verb again and it's \nmore polite than screw up."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 248.049,
    "endTime": 256.68,
    "text": "And another phrase you can use is 'by mistake'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 260.54,
    "endTime": 261.94,
    "text": "Urgh!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.0,
    "endTime": 262.84,
    "text": "What?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.96,
    "endTime": 265.14,
    "text": "I drank your coffee by mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 265.14,
    "endTime": 268.36,
    "text": "How much sugar is in that?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 268.36,
    "endTime": 269.94,
    "text": "5 teaspoons."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 269.94,
    "endTime": 273.51,
    "text": "I like it sweet."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.51,
    "endTime": 278.0,
    "text": "So 'by mistake' means 'by accident'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 278.0,
    "endTime": 279.37,
    "text": "Hi."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 279.37,
    "endTime": 280.75,
    "text": "Hi."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 280.75,
    "endTime": 282.46,
    "text": "Your pay check has arrived."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 282.46,
    "endTime": 284.09,
    "text": "Oh good."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 284.09,
    "endTime": 285.09,
    "text": "Hey!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 285.09,
    "endTime": 287.57,
    "text": "Somebody's already opened this."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 287.57,
    "endTime": 292.71999999999997,
    "text": "Yeah, sorry, I opened it by mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 292.72,
    "endTime": 298.53000000000003,
    "text": "You didn't earn as much as me last month."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 298.53,
    "endTime": 301.46999999999997,
    "text": "So by mistake - by accident."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 301.47,
    "endTime": 305.59000000000003,
    "text": "By mistake means you didn't intend to do\nit."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.59,
    "endTime": 307.78999999999996,
    "text": "Or did you?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 307.79,
    "endTime": 313.44,
    "text": "Now the word mistake is a noun here, but it\ncan be a verb too."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 313.44,
    "endTime": 316.63,
    "text": "And then it means you think one thing is another."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 316.63,
    "endTime": 323.84,
    "text": "For example, you have to keep your pills safe\nbecause children might mistake them for candy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 323.84,
    "endTime": 332.03999999999996,
    "text": "Mistake is an irregular verb – mistake,\nmistook, mistaken."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 332.05,
    "endTime": 334.16,
    "text": "Oh Mary."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.16,
    "endTime": 335.28000000000003,
    "text": "Do we know each other?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 335.28,
    "endTime": 338.35999999999996,
    "text": "Oh sorry, I mistook you for someone else."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 338.36,
    "endTime": 339.88,
    "text": "No problem."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 339.88,
    "endTime": 345.64,
    "text": "I mistook you for someone else means I thought\nyou were one person, but you were another."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 345.64,
    "endTime": 349.13,
    "text": "Yes, it sounds a little formal to me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 349.13,
    "endTime": 353.75,
    "text": "I think normally I'd say it differently."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 353.75,
    "endTime": 355.44,
    "text": "Oh Mary."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 355.44,
    "endTime": 356.88,
    "text": "Do we know each other?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 356.88,
    "endTime": 359.52,
    "text": "Oh sorry I thought you were someone else."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 359.52,
    "endTime": 361.07,
    "text": "No problem."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 361.07,
    "endTime": 362.90999999999997,
    "text": "That sounded more natural."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 362.91,
    "endTime": 368.22,
    "text": "Yes, and there's another thing we often\nsay when we've made a mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 368.22,
    "endTime": 369.22,
    "text": "What?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 369.22,
    "endTime": 370.22,
    "text": "Sorry."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 370.22,
    "endTime": 374.87,
    "text": "Let's look at how we do that."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 374.87,
    "endTime": 376.17,
    "text": "Who designed these calendars?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 376.17,
    "endTime": 377.17,
    "text": "Oh I did."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 377.17,
    "endTime": 379.0,
    "text": "Do you like them?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 379.0,
    "endTime": 380.74,
    "text": "How many copies did you print?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 380.74,
    "endTime": 382.1,
    "text": "I don't know."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 382.1,
    "endTime": 384.52000000000004,
    "text": "I ordered 500."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 384.52,
    "endTime": 386.26,
    "text": "Is there a problem?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 386.26,
    "endTime": 387.26,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 387.26,
    "endTime": 388.26,
    "text": "Look at February."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 388.26,
    "endTime": 389.26,
    "text": "There are 30 days."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 389.26,
    "endTime": 390.26,
    "text": "Oh, it's a mistake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 390.26,
    "endTime": 393.06,
    "text": "I'm so sorry Kathy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 393.06,
    "endTime": 394.06,
    "text": "It's my fault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 394.06,
    "endTime": 395.4,
    "text": "I didn't notice."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 395.4,
    "endTime": 397.46,
    "text": "It's my fault too."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 397.46,
    "endTime": 400.38,
    "text": "I didn't check it before it went to the\nprinters."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 400.38,
    "endTime": 403.56,
    "text": "We're both at fault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 403.56,
    "endTime": 405.66,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 405.66,
    "endTime": 410.319,
    "text": "30 days!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 410.319,
    "endTime": 413.49,
    "text": "Now here's a very useful phrase."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 413.49,
    "endTime": 418.90000000000003,
    "text": "When we say 'it's my fault', we're\nsaying we're responsible."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 418.9,
    "endTime": 422.0,
    "text": "We accept the blame for what went wrong."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 422.0,
    "endTime": 425.13,
    "text": "We admit we did the wrong thing."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 425.13,
    "endTime": 431.1,
    "text": "And if we don't want to accept responsibility,\nwe can use the negative."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 434.06,
    "endTime": 435.54,
    "text": "You need to do this again."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 435.55,
    "endTime": 436.55,
    "text": "Why?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 436.55,
    "endTime": 439.97,
    "text": "It's full of spelling mistakes\nIt's not my fault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 439.97,
    "endTime": 444.11,
    "text": "My spell checker doesn't work\nThen use a dictionary."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 444.11,
    "endTime": 445.31,
    "text": "Humph."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 445.31,
    "endTime": 449.05,
    "text": "So 'it's not my fault' means it's\nnot my responsibility."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 449.05,
    "endTime": 451.91,
    "text": "Don't blame me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 451.91,
    "endTime": 458.25,
    "text": "Fault is an uncountable noun here, so it has\nno plural form."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 458.25,
    "endTime": 461.92,
    "text": "But the word fault has other meanings where\nit's countable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 461.92,
    "endTime": 463.38,
    "text": "For example?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 463.38,
    "endTime": 467.84,
    "text": "Well, people can have faults."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 467.84,
    "endTime": 469.4,
    "text": "Good luck with your presentation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 469.4,
    "endTime": 470.78,
    "text": "Are you nervous?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 470.78,
    "endTime": 473.32,
    "text": "No, I'm going to be fantastic."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 473.32,
    "endTime": 475.58,
    "text": "They'll love me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 475.58,
    "endTime": 482.21,
    "text": "Jay may have some faults, but lack of confidence\nisn't one of them."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 482.21,
    "endTime": 489.60999999999996,
    "text": "So here faults is plural and it means the\nbad or weak parts of someone's character."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.61,
    "endTime": 493.23,
    "text": "I don't really have many faults."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 493.23,
    "endTime": 495.02000000000004,
    "text": "Yeah right."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 495.02,
    "endTime": 498.99,
    "text": "And faults can also mean other things that\nare wrong."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 498.99,
    "endTime": 502.02,
    "text": "Machines can have faults."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 502.02,
    "endTime": 504.64,
    "text": "Faults are things that stop them working correctly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 504.64,
    "endTime": 506.84,
    "text": "A fault in the design."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 506.84,
    "endTime": 509.78,
    "text": "A structural fault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 513.149,
    "endTime": 515.26,
    "text": "You need to use the other copier."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 515.26,
    "endTime": 516.91,
    "text": "This one's not working."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 516.91,
    "endTime": 517.91,
    "text": "Really?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 517.91,
    "endTime": 518.91,
    "text": "Why not?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 518.91,
    "endTime": 522.48,
    "text": "They think it's an electrical fault."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 522.48,
    "endTime": 523.5600000000001,
    "text": "Hmmm."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 524.39,
    "endTime": 525.86,
    "text": "Told you."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 525.87,
    "endTime": 530.15,
    "text": "OK, I think it's time to review, don't\nyou?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 530.15,
    "endTime": 534.02,
    "text": "Yes, let's see what you can remember."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 534.02,
    "endTime": 541.89,
    "text": "When we make a mistake, the first thing we\nsay is often an expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 541.89,
    "endTime": 543.83,
    "text": "Or an expletive."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 543.83,
    "endTime": 548.34,
    "text": "An expletive is usually a swear word or curse\nword."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 548.34,
    "endTime": 551.84,
    "text": "But there are some more polite alternatives."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 551.84,
    "endTime": 558.36,
    "text": "For example in the UK we could say 'Oh bother!'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 558.36,
    "endTime": 561.82,
    "text": "And in the US we could say 'Oh shoot!'"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 561.82,
    "endTime": 569.86,
    "text": "Here's a really useful one: Oh damn!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 569.86,
    "endTime": 575.98,
    "text": "We usually use the word mistake with the verb\nmake."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 575.98,
    "endTime": 582.73,
    "text": "And we use phrasal verbs too like 'I've\nscrewed up'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 582.73,
    "endTime": 588.09,
    "text": "And we can also say 'I've messed up'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 588.09,
    "endTime": 596.22,
    "text": "If we think we're responsible for a mistake\nwe'll say 'It's my fault'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 596.22,
    "endTime": 600.63,
